cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the need for enhancement of data rate in wireless networks and proposes a compression algorithm for CPRI links, which is a crucial component of Centralized Radio Access Network (C-RAN) architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper utilizes Lloyd algorithm for codebook training and investigates methods to vectorize I/Q samples, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper focuses on improving the effective data rate of CPRI links, which are used for communication between remote radio heads and baseband units in C-RAN architecture. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a solution for reducing codebook search complexity and codebook size, which can be considered as a control problem. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the performance of the proposed compression algorithm in terms of Error Vector Magnitude (EVM) distortion, which is a metric commonly used in multimedia applications.
